{"key":"processedPost-16698408","value":{"id":16698408,"first":16695183,"last":20638892,"when":1344964793,"utime":"08/14/12 08:19 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>itsthezane said:</b><br />Yeaa but I feel like being able to PC the petri dish itself and not have to pour would help lower contam chances. I suppose I could just use 1/2 pints for that though<br /></blockquote><br /><br />That's not how it's done.&nbsp; Pouring a petri and then sterilizing is a great way for all your agar to boil over and spill into the PC.&nbsp; This is why we sterilize a bottle of agar and then pour in sterile conditions.<br /><br />Using jars is a further waste of money and materials.&nbsp; I can only imagine the financial expense, mess, and shelf space requirements if I had several hundred 1/2 pint jars stacked up rather than petri dishes.<br /><br />At 15 cents each, just use petri dishes.&nbsp; After use, find a kid to give them to for keeping their bugs and other treasures.<br />RR","title":"Re: Plastic petri dishes in PC!","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}